description:
&lt;p&gt;The ‘Lancashire Chest Centre’ offers tertiary services in several sub-specialties of Respiratory and Sleep Medicine. You will be joining a thriving team which comprises of 10 Respiratory&lt;em&gt; C&lt;/em&gt;onsultants across the two hospital sites. This post is based at Lancashire Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust. Services are provided across both Chorley and Preston sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently have an outstanding opportunity for a suitably qualified highly experienced Senior Respiratory Physiologist to take the lead for the Sleep Physiology service. We are looking to recruit a highly motivated, experienced and adaptable individual.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for you to use your clinical and leadership skills to operationally lead and support the department, ensuring our services run smoothly and efficiently whilst continuously striving to improve and develop the service for the future needs of the patient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview: 5th December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
